The "Langtang Mafia" is a rumored clique of military men from Langtang, Plateau State who hold or have held positions of power in the Nigerian government. The term is often used in reference to the 1985 â€“ 1993 Babangida junta. Purported members include Lt Gen Joshua Nimyel Dogonyaro (rtd), Lt Gen Jeremiah Useni (rtd), Lt. Gen Domkat Bali (rtd) and Brig Gen John Nanzip Shagaya (rtd and presently Senator)
